==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Denudation
<hw>Den`u*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>denudatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧nudation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of stripping off covering, or removing the
surface; a making bare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The laying bare of rocks by the
washing away of the overlying earth, etc.; or the excavation and removal
of them by the action of running water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Denude</ent>⟦br⟧
